The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Travoltas night life

 CATHERINE ELSWORTH

 London, June 14: John Travolta has revealed his secret for avoiding the paparazzi staying up all night and sleeping through much of the day.

 The Hollywood star said that he routinely remained up until 7am and his wife and children had adopted his nocturnal ways to protect their privacy.

 Were like the Addams family or the Munsters, living sort of an odd, nocturnal life, Travolta, famous for his roles in Grease, Saturday Night Fever and Pulp Fiction, told the American magazine Parade.

 THE DAILY TELEGRAPH




